+# PR-214 Review Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The triage source of truth was `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`. `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was not used as authority.
+
+## Changes Applied
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Kept preview metadata fields in a shared payload for both live and fallback responses.
+- Ensured the fallback response includes:
+  - `approval_state`
+  - `requires_human_review`
+  - `status: "preview_unavailable"`
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- Normalized incoming approval states through `normalize_approval_state(...)` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+- Verified that `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` now emits `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Extended the existing fallback test to assert the preserved review-state fields.
+- Added a regression test covering the manual-review normalization path on the fallback payload.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback example to show the corrected payload fields.
+- Replaced the stale note with the current downstream-consumer rationale for keeping normalized `approval_state` in fallback responses.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+```text
+.....
+----------------------------------------------------------------------
+Ran 5 tests in 0.000s
+
+OK
+```
+
+Direct runtime check:
+
+```python
